3:
The enemy has pursued my soul;
\q he has pushed me down to the ground;
\q he has made me to live in darkness like those who have been dead for ages.
\q

5:
I call to mind the old days;
\q I meditate on all your deeds;
\q I reflect on your accomplishments.
\q

6:
I spread my hands out to you in prayer;
\q my soul thirsts for you in a parched land.
\qs Selah\qs*

9:
Rescue me from my enemies, Yahweh;
\q I flee to you to hide.
\q

11:
Yahweh, for your name's sake, keep me alive;
\q in your righteousness bring my soul out of trouble.
\q
